caption: Nice small restaurant with quality seafood at a median price. Sushi was fresh and tasty and the hubby even enjoyed my favorites the butter scallops and baked mussels which he doesn't care too much for in general. Friendly atmosphere but the service is a bit slow. Over the course of an hour and a half we did not receive all of our food. Just give yourself some time to dine here just in case for a 5 star experience. We'll definitely return when we we aren't on a time crunch.

Everything we got was delicious! We called for carry out and it was ready in 20 minutes. The calamari, gyoza, emperor maki and aloha maki were all amazing. They even threw in miso soup with the order.
Good
Super fresh sushi, really good lunch sets.

We absolutely loved Ginza Sushi. Everything was perfect, just a miscommunication at the beginning when we ordered appetizers and out waitress thought we ordered only one when we actually ordered 3. Food/sushi is delicious! Definitely RECOMMEND this restaurant to anyone who LOVES sushi!

Read the bill carefully before you pay. We were charged an extra 30% for gratuity on the bill without being informed. Food was amazing but every one got their food at separate times so the first person was finished before the last one had gotten their food. Three stars is being generous.

It's a great place to enjoy variety of rolled sushi, that the most varieties of local chefs can offer. I'd refrain from commenting some negatives I noticed.  Service was great that I want to support this place
Awesome service.

Ginza Sushi is a great place to eat! Russell and his team take care of you and make you feel at home. Ginza is clean, cozy, Covid safety conscious, and the food is delicious! Been coming here for a while and will most definitely be back.
Amazing sushi at an amazing price! Staff is super friendly and very professional. This is my go to place for my cheat meal sushi.  Recommend the Hawaiian, aloha and avenger rolls.
Shumai looked pretty in plate. However, it was under-cooked and I tasted raw flour. Cooked parts tasted good.

This place is the best sushi in all of the islands. I would blindfold someone and tell them they were in Japan and take them here, they wouldn’t know any different. Amazing customer service and amazing food. As a sushi connoisseur myself I am very harsh on bad sushi. But this is in my opinion is the best sushi ever.  Prove me wrong.

The only place I will get sushi on island! The staff is so friendly and remembers your name if you’re a frequent customer, such as myself. Amazing food and sushi and convenient location! Look no further for your sushi cravings!!!
Delicious and great service
Amazing food & fast service!
Amazing Sushi.
Even with the COVID-19 restrictions this place was amazing. The customer service was top notch and the sushi was perfect. I will definitely be a returning customer.
Dine in available. Food is great and service is top notch.
The Food is outstanding!! The people are full of Aloha! Can't wait for my next visit!
Best sushi I have had so far in Hawaii.

This is by far my favorite sushi restaurant in downtown Honolulu. There’s sushi is spot on the owner and chef is the most genuine wonderful person on island. I walk here almost every night and if I don’t walk here I order it as this is just so delectable!!! It’s a must try!! They are always so welcoming and they do everything in their power to take care of your pup as well sitting outside. This is just the BEST sushi place!
Got the omakase, sashimi plate and a roll. Everything was fresh and delicious and paired well with a nigori sake. Staff was nice and helpful in choosing the sake. Will definitely be returning

The best sushi I’ve ever had, every time I go here it’s the exact perfection each time. Russell is always so kind, and attentive. This place has wonderful customer service and business practices. My favorite thing to order is the Nbious Maki and an order of Inari. Once you try their sushi you won’t go anywhere else!
Always quality in service and food.  Highly recommended!
Love the homey vibes. Owner is very personable and helpful. Trying to support local businesses! Love the sushi selections and miso butterfish!
Delicious!
Great place and easy parking. Melt in your mouth sushi!

Amazing food and amazing service definitely my favorite sushi place. The staff is very good with social distancing and making sure everything is sanitised and a safe clean environment for people who wish to dine in. Have been here twice already and plan to visit many more times!
Russ/Lawrence is the best!!!

LOVE, LOVE, LOVE this place!! The service is phenomenal, Russell is always so attentive and caring. My son and i have been here 3-4 times and have loved it every time. And each time we've been here we've had a great experience. Today my son, he's 10 made "The Chris". He absolutely loved it! Tempura shrimp, soft shell crab, and cucumber. He said it was so yummy. This place is a must try!! Go for it :-) we will definitely come again!
Super friendly. Food is exceptional. Good to support local businesses
Fresh, good quality fish and authentic ingredients. Friendly and accommodating staff—they remember you, too. Great neighborhood place in an urban setting.

Everything is good!!! Great service! I really love their Avengers roll. Obsessed. Friendly fast service and they always give you an aloha bonus gift. Check their IG for the daily also bonus. Curbside and take out both available.
My favorite place for sushi in Honolulu! The food and service are over the top!
Best sushi I've had on any of the islands!!! 😍😍😍 amazing service & caring owner.
Loved this place! Met the owner and was introduced to some new items! Definitely get the otoro!
The best sushi restaurant I have been too. All around great experience with an amazing server, and fantastic food. Would recommend to anyone everytime, and will 100% go back!
Great place to have some local Sushi! Definitely recommend to all. Great food and great service!

I love coming back to this place every time I visit the island. The service is great, the food is amazingly delicious, and it has a nice vibe. I felt like I was back in Japan. Dynamite roll is a must try!
2nd time for dinner. Love this little spot. Service and food were terrific ! Thank you !
Delicious sushi, especially with scallops 🔥🔥🔥 great service. Thank you for soy sauce smile for our baby-girl)

Good fresh sushi and lots of variety for a small place. Pretty nice inside. The waiter struggles with friendliness but he gives good service and isn't rude. Go for the good food at decent prices- not the jokes

Great food, very friendly and helpful staff 🙂
This place was amazing! The sushi was nice and fresh and tasted amazing! I highly recommend!
Great food and atmosphere as the waiter staff made us feel at home!
Everything we had was fantastic, highly recommend Nbious roll!

A restaurant located within Ward Village by the Ward Centre. The restaurant is along Auahi Street along the row of restaurants connected to the parking structure. We were greeted immediately and or ordered placed quickly. The staff is friendly. The food is flavorful with the tempura ice cream being exceptional. Great place to visit.

This place is bomb for the bomb staff and food. Must come sushi joint if you're in Oahu. Super relaxed and zen environment. Weight staff is amazing and one of them had these great one liners that made me appreciate the restaurant even more. I can't remember the last time I had a dining experience so fun like this. I had the omakse plate and felt like the quality was amazing. Good portion for the price! Calamari was amazing too! Tea is definitely house made. The cups are ordered from Japan. They all sell them at the restaurant for ~12 each. I hope to come back here again!!
Excellent awesome food and great service 👍🙏don't think twice about it
2nd time there in 3 days Russell is a great server

Best sushi I’ve had on Oahu &, trust me, I’ve been searching! The service was also phenomenal.. We had the chicken katsu, avenger roll, emperor roll, beauty/beast roll & garlic crunch.. amazing. Btw, please try the plum wine!
The food here is great! This is one of our favorite sushi places in Oahu! Great service as well! Fast, clean and our favorite rolls is the bomb and captain crunch roll!
Awesome as usual! Never disappoints!
Service was good, sushi was also good

I tried the BBB combo, with sushi, sashimi, and butterfish. It is served with salad and miso soup. It was pretty tasty. You won't be disappointed.

Awesome 😃 food and service were excellent! Server mentioned that they had a Toro special so I ordered that with a bunch of other appetizers, I saved it for last and it was sooooo ono!!! Definitely going back 😁🤙
Best sushi and udon

I've been coming here for awhile. I think before the name changed it was called Ninja Sushi. This is one of my nostalgic stops I make while in Honolulu. The maki is always on point here. The employees are also super nice!
Very good value & quality
Taste of food was excellent.   Presentation of food was lovely.  Small seating area, but nice atmosphere with pleasant background music.  Very enjoyable meal.
Some of the best sushi I had in a long time.  Everything was fresh and the staff, I have to say they are very nice and professional.

Very much enjoyed our food. The restaurant owner was very informative and personable as well as funny. Otoro was melt-in-your-mouth amazing. I'm excited to go again!

Sushi is not bad at all, prices are decent. Service was great the two times I've been here.

Fabulous service and food.
Excellent sushi, and I'm not easily impressed.

Really a great find: thank you other Google reviewers! The sushi was indeed very fresh and very tasty. I also appreciated how they don't make oversized rolls - the pieces fit into your mouth! My favorite part of the meal was the mussel miso soup: I ordered it twice in one meal. The fresh spring mix salad included a variety of veggies but a bit overpriced for what it was. Service was excellent: he was very friendly and efficient. Price-wise, this restaurant is very affordable for the excellent quality of food. A couple bucks more than one would pay for pre-made sushi at Whole Foods but a whole lot better. This restaurant is also in a great spot of Honolulu, an easy walk to Ward Theaters, Ala Moana Beach Park, and several free parking garages. Perhaps the only downside is the fact that the restroom is outside of the restaurant in the adjacent Ward shopping center. Not a huge problem for us but may pose an issue for those with disabilities or with small children.
Very good food indeed
This place is relatively small but the food and service is outstanding!

The Ginza Sushi is a great sushi eatery. Clean, comfortable and everyone there were friendly, helpful and the service was quick. I am coming back...today's order was 2 pcs of uni temaki and a natto roll for my 92 yr old mother's birthday meal. She had the biggest smile when she saw the two uni temaki pieces. Smiles from ear to ear. She said its the best birthday present! A taste of Tokyo...for my 92 yr old mother!! Thank you, Ginza Sushi.
Food and service were excellent.  The lunch menu has a great variety and reasonable size portions.  The only challenge was finding parking near the restaurant at lunch time.  Great experience.
Get the omakasu, it will change your life.
So good. Excellent food and service. It was slow and the guy talked to us and told us what was good. Super cool place.
Very fresh fish and accommodating staff. Reasonable prices.
Loved it, the food and staff were wonderful

Excellent! Reasonably priced clean and very friendly place to grab some sushi, rolls and other items. While you there you should try the lichen sake as it is really good. The food is made to order and therefore it is always fresh and sometimes when it's really busy definitely worth the wait. It's my favorite spot on the island.

I consider myself a finder of the best sushi wherever I go. I’ve eaten sushi in Florida, Wisconsin, Texas, California, South Korea, etc... etc... several places, multiple cities. This by far is the best sushi I’ve ever had. On top of that, the owner was very friendly and funny. Kept me laughing and made the experience great! I’ve been several places where the price heavily outweighed the quality of the food(sushi) served. This was the complete opposite. The prices were very fair compared to how fresh and how exceptionally well prepared the meal was. Great job! Awesome!

Price for quality and service, leans more on the service side. If you care about quality, this is not the place. Service is good that if you bring family and friends they will be treated well. They might not have deals like yanagi and  king, but i would rather spend more and eat here instead. Then again I'm all about quality over service. Sadly there are better places.
Great service and delicious sushi
always a delight to eat at this place, highly recommended
Better that genki but you will pay for it
Great place
It's  very delicious, always fresh and very clean. The owner is very friendly and helpful. I strongly recommend. It's our favorite place and resonal price.
Love eating here. The owner is really nice and always puts a smile on me and my wife's face. Their portions are good and their quality is great as well. Please come eat here and support local.

Owner is the nicest man ever! He welcomes you to the restaurant and has no problem making you feel comfortable and ensure that you enjoy your meal.  The menu is pretty extensive and very reasonably priced. There are so many variations of rolls to try... be adventurous and try something you never had. My personal favorite is the Avenger roll.

Best place for sushi in Kaka'ako!!! Service is always prompt and super friendly. Fresh nigiri and inventive rolls in a relaxed atmosphere make it a perfect setting to savor each bite. Great variety for Sake as well. Best kept secret in the area!! Will keep coming back!!!
Consistantly great food.
Fantastic Food and the service was exceptional! Finally found a great sushi spot with great service ! Highly recommended !

Really, really great sushi and friendly staff. Not super fast, but not too slow either. Try the Bomb, Hurricane, and Garlic Crunch rolls - the flavor is right on and rolls are large with 8 pieces. Prices are reasonable, between $10-15 per roll - if they were $8-13 this would be five stars every time .
Always a pleasure - tasty and friendly - a great place for a meal.

Best freaking sushi I had in a long time. Deserves the 5 stars and more. Rainbow roll and salmon lover was the bomb. Also try the handrolls. And by far, one of the best things of this place is the owner. Friendliest and nicest person you will ever have the pleasure of meeting.
Amazing service

Great place. The food is tasty and there's good value also.  Is it the absolute best sushi? No, but you'd be hard pressed to find anything better at this price.  There are some "lovers" plates full of salmon or hamachi. Those are terrific.

These guys know how to infuse a lot of flavor into their rolls! Tried the Ginza Special (pictured) , the Bomb (worth the little extra time) and the Beauty & the Beast with unagi substitution for a perfect dinner :)
Delicious food and great service!

This is the best sushi I’ve ever had!! We walked in the door and just the smell was enough to sell me on the place! I ordered the Bomb sushi and it was THE BOMB! My boyfriend ordered the Garlic Crunch and it was also amazing! Highly recommend this place! Amazing food at a decent price! 😍
Owner kind and pleasant. Avengers maki is amazing

Food and service was awesome! A gem in Ward Village.

Good service, great value for the price. Sashimi combo saves you some money vs Ala carte and the aloha roll is thoughtfully prepared. Great flavour profiles. The main ingredients are not hidden  by too much accent, they are the star of the show.
I got very poor service and when I spoke go the owner he didn't seem concerned at all, I hope the food is a 1 because they get an f in service

Amazing experience. The food was so very delicious. I can't wait to go back. Get location. Park across the street better and bigger (TJ max parking structure). Service was excellent and funny and so polite. Not a long wait for the food. Great portions.
This place is excellent!  The sushi tasted very fresh and was made with artistry.  Very small inside that is comfortable.
Great food at reasonable prices. Super friendly owner and excellent service. We'll be back to try more of the menu.
Great sushi! Great people!

Great sushi at great prices. Ever since our favorite sushi place closed we have been looking for a good place. We finally found it here! The owner is a wonderful guy and very attentive to his customers. Try the lychee sake and tell your waiter Anna sent you!

This is our go-to place for lunch or dinner at Ward. Reasonable, consistent flavors, fresh sashimi...and Echigo beer (!). The owner always makes you feel welcome; love this little Japanese restaurant!
